</m:math>, where <emphasis effect="italics">p′</emphasis> is the sample proportion, <emphasis effect="italics">q′</emphasis> = 1 – <emphasis effect="italics">p′</emphasis>, and <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> is the sample size.</item>
<item>Solving for <emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis> gives you an equation for the sample size.</item>
<item>
 <m:math>
 <m:mrow>
